detaileddescription.para: Replaces comments in a VORBIS_COMMENT block with a new one.
For convenience, a trailing NUL is added to the entry if it doesn't have one already.

Depending on the the value of all, either all or just the first comment whose field name(s) match the given entry's name will be replaced by the given entry. If no comments match, entry will simply be appended.
If copy is true, a copy of the entry is stored; otherwise, the object takes ownership of the entry.entry pointer.

simplesect.para: If this function returns false, the caller still owns the pointer.

parameterdescription.para: A pointer to an existing VORBIS_COMMENT object.
The comment to insert.

If true, all comments whose field name matches entry's field name will be removed, and entry will be inserted at the position of the first matching comment. If false, only the first comment whose field name matches entry's field name will be replaced with entry.
See above. object!=NULL object->type==FLAC__METADATA_TYPE_VORBIS_COMMENT (entry.entry!=NULL&&entry.length>0)|| (entry.entry==NULL&&entry.length==0&&copy==false)
false if memory allocation fails or entry does not comply with the Vorbis comment specification, else true.

false if realloc() fails, else true.
